##The road back to work for a small factory owner

The function introduction by "CAIJING" Magazine Company Industry Report team to create, discuss the success or failure of the enterprise, explore the rise and fall of the industry, promote sunshine business

The following article is from I am Nanqi Dao, the author of Nanqi Dao

Focus on entrepreneurship and investment methodology

The outbreak caught small and micro businesses like Tsai off guard. And the road to work is a long way off

The outbreak caught small and micro businesses like Tsai off guard. And the road to work is a long way off

East of the South Seven

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Small factories are everywhere in Guangdong Province (south seventh road, 2019)

Affected by the epidemic, recently including KTV Wu Hai, Xibeijia Guolong, and the chairman of Laoxiang Chicken Shu Congxuan, have all come forward to say that they will not survive for more than 2-3 months, but in fact, their scale is not small, more difficult than them are small business owners. They don't have tens of millions of dollars on their books, they don't have micro blogs, they don't have public relations, all they can do is wait.
Lao Cai has a factory in Bao'an District, Shenzhen, which specializes in wire processing, mainly used in audio cables, charging cables, headphone cables and so on. It is a small factory, with 3-40 employees and a yearly output value of less than ten million. Such companies abound in Shenzhen and Dongguan.
The outbreak caught small and micro businesses like Tsai off guard. And the road to work is a long way off.

The outbreak caught small and micro businesses like Tsai off guard. And the road to work is a long way off.

Registration:

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Application for resumption of work

In the current situation, epidemic prevention has become a top priority for governments at all levels. Reporting and auditing for work under epidemic conditions has become a physical and mental activity.
The first is to send people to the training course, "how to start and prepare. ". The factory environment is then sanitized and monitored. FOR LODGEMENT OF INSTRUMENTS AND APPLICATION INFORMATION:
In Bao'an District, a factory has to apply to start work, first in the face of a sea of forms and documents, including:

Application form for resumption of work
Commitment Letter of epidemic prevention and control in the re-work enterprises
3 Company Prevention and control team
4. Employee temperature records
5 protective equipment distribution registration form
6. Inventory of protective equipment
71 Personnel Flow Information Sheet
72 list of people on the move
8. Factory wide checklist
9. factory-by-factory responsibility book signing
10. Corporate Preparedness for an outbreak
11 rehabilitation training files for all employees
12 pre-security workshop
Isolation Room 13

In Xili Subdistrict, Shenzhen, some companies received a street office to resume work, the need for the company for each employee every day to prepare a suit of protective clothing, finally found that not only enterprises can not buy, there are no hospitals, so do not. Even there is a very magical situation: enterprises to resume work, they have to submit information application, stamped with the official seal. But the seal is in the office. The office is sealed. And the paperwork wasn't filed. But you can't get into the office unless you give us something.
"We didn't apply to resume work, and the application will not be approved, " says Cai, who also works in Bao'an District but knows his friends are chasing a wild goose chase. The first is the complexity of the approval process, approval rate is low, so many factories have abandoned the declaration. Officials at a factory in Bao'an District, Shenzhen, said they had submitted twice but failed. There are more than 40,000 companies, including many listed companies such as tencent's Xunlei, in Shenzhen's famous Yuehai Street office, but only about 100 pass through in a day.

Worker:

Even though it was finally approved, the workers were a big problem, and the factory was facing a shortage of workers.
The same is the policy to the grass-roots level, has been layer upon layer of code and distortion of the status quo. Although the Ministry of Public Security and the National Development and Reform Commission have written regulations, they are not allowed to block freeways, county roads or township roads at will. But the actual situation is, now the provinces, cities, counties and townships, have been artificial with dirt, walls, railings blockade into an isolated island. No one gets in, no one gets out.
Lao Cai's workers came from places like Hubei, Hunan, Jiangxi, and Sichuan, not to mention Hubei, where the outbreak was severe. Hunan Cili and other non-key epidemic areas, these workers want to go out to work, only to find that even the countryside can not go out, the road to the county has been completely cut off. This kind of situation has occurred in many places such as Sichuan. Old Workers can't get out, and there's no way to replace them.
Even if some of the workers have returned to Shenzhen, they dare not start work. At the industrial park where Cai works, workers are first quarantined for 14 days. Then, after approval, if one worker is found to have a fever during the work period, whether diagnosed or not, then the plant is shut down and everyone is quarantined for 14 days. If the upstream and downstream suppliers are working during the quarantine and they have not yet lifted the quarantine, it is likely that the partners will change suppliers because they can not afford to wait.
If so, then don't start at all and wait.

Supply Chain:

Now manufacturing production, has been a supply chain, industrial chain deep cooperation of the ecological integration of the relationship, no matter how small a commodity, it is impossible to complete alone. According to the habit of manufacturing, considering the Spring Festival holiday, usually before the year, prepare 15 days of production raw materials, up to a month, too much storage will have too much pressure. It's a chain of events, one of which isn't working at all, but it requires multiple partners in the entire supply chain, all working together.
Lao Cai's factory produces a common-looking sound cable, including the core part of the fiber optic, PVC plastic, metal wire, terminal open mold, tape, packaging. Each part requires a supplier and a small processing plant. It requires at least six suppliers, and Lao Cai himself is only a tiny part of the outsourced industrial chain of big brands such as LG. Even if it's as powerful as the IPHONE, if one of the screw suppliers doesn't open, then the rest of the screen and other components of an iPhone aren't in place to complete the final assembly and get into circulation.
Modern business cooperation, let each other more and more close cooperation, but also the degree of dependence on others more and more. And the quantity of goods in the manufacturing industry has a direct impact on e-commerce and foreign trade business. It is no exaggeration to say that when China coughs, the world catches a cold. Foreign Trade Ella, mainly do Europe's Amazon, home electronics, but now the goods, only until mid-february, now orders, the factory can not restock. Can only wait, and in this process, the ranking of the net shop that she manages painstakingly and heat can drop, can affect next phase revenue again.

Triangle debt:

The plight of small and micro manufacturing enterprises, ostensibly affected by the epidemic, but behind the deep-seated problem, in fact, is triangular debt. Triangle debt is the biggest stubborn disease of China's manufacturing industry, the problem has a long history, deep into each link of the industrial chain. The taiwanese-led business model has made domestic manufacturers miserable, but unable to change it. Owing each other money has become an industry rule. In Europe and the United States, the developed countries, generally cash settlement, while there will be legal constraints and provisions. In addition to chips and other high-tech threshold industry, must pay cash outside. The lower the threshold of the industry, the more serious debt, vicious circle.
The big producers go to medium-sized factories to do the work for them, the medium-sized enterprises get the orders, they get the raw materials on credit first, and then they subcontract to the small enterprises, and the small enterprises subcontract to the micro-factories and the family workshops, large manufacturers receive goods to resellers and e-commerce platform, one link after another. Payment is usually made 2-6 months after receipt of the goods. So everyone is a creditor, everyone owes the embarrassing situation.
Many low-end manufacturing enterprises in large numbers, sometimes between each other in order to compete for business, will desperately low prices, even at a loss to rob customers. This exposes the problem of Chinese industrial structure. When companies face low profits, they crowd out working capital and payments, further exacerbating mutual defaults. However, there is no core technology threshold for enterprise products, which leads to product backlog and leads to the form of purchasing. If one of them fails, its debts to the other partners fail, setting off a chain of bankruptcies. A vicious cycle in the ecological chain.
Chinese factories typically have a billing period of three to six months. If it is a big company such as Huawei Orders, accounting period of 60 days, you first for Huawei production, procurement of raw materials and wages, after delivery, 60 days back payment, before all the funds have enterprises advance. For a company as strong as Huawei, the risks are relatively small, but for other companies, the risks are huge. At the end of 2015, the 4,000-employee Shenzhen zhongtianxin Electronics Co. , a contract manufacturer for hammer mobile phones, lost its boss because of a triangle of debts, triggering a series of partner manufacturers to close down.
Cai's profit is very thin, a year of ten million level, but in addition to rent, utilities, wages, other administrative expenses, that is, every month left a few tens of thousands of dollars in profit, even if this profit is also receivables. Years Ago, rent, salary, bonus, stock, pay part of the purchase, in fact, the book cash has been left, waiting for the new year after the settlement and flow. "restaurants and KTV are all cash flow, and we rarely receive cash. Most factories have cash on their books that, if they don't start work at all, will last one month, two months at most. "
